history.content: I'm a recent L&S transfer and am trying to declare CS by the end of this school year. I took CS61A over the summer and am currently taking CS61B, CS70 and DATA 8. I'm deciding between CS 61C, EE 16A/16B, (plus a third general education class) and whether or not to take 2 at once. I've already taken Linear Algebra at my community college, but I don't remember parts of the content nor do I know much about circuits. I'm considering taking 61C + 16B and self learning the circuits, but I worry it will be too much. Any advice or class recommendations would be greatly appreciated!
history.subject: Course Load as Intended CS Transfer
